According to the court document, both charges could end with a death sentence.
Weeks after the attack, an expanded federal courthouse filed a 22-point indictment to Saipov, including eight counts of murder involving racketeering, commonly used by federal prosecutors in organised crime cases, as well as charges of violence and destruction of vehicles.
